      "created_at": "2016-05-03 06:30:49 UTC",
      "updated_at": "2016-05-03 06:30:49 UTC",
      "body": "80 chars, asides from being the old traditional max column, is also the\nmaximum for viewing files and diffs in GitHub on mobile. On bigger screens\nthat default jumps up to 112. So if you're going to bump it up, 112 columns\nis another option.\n\nOn Tue, 3 May 2016, 07:25 Ólafur Páll Geirsson, <notifications@github.com>\nwrote:\n\n> I see many OSS repos use a different coding style from the scalafmt\n> default style\n>\n>    - --maxColumn 100 (scala.js + scalafmt are the only repos I've seen\n>    look nicely with 80 character limit)\n>    - --continuationIndentCallSite 2\n>    - --assumeStdLibStripMargin false\n>\n> —\n> You are receiving this because you are subscribed to this thread.\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> <https://github.com/olafurpg/scalafmt/issues/202>\n>\n"
    },
