      "updated_at": "2016-05-03 06:44:12 UTC",
      "body": "I agree, I will continue to use 80 chars for my own code.\r\n\r\nMy concern is that most people just install scalafmt, run it on their repo, see their lines break at odd places (e.g., a return type is 80+ char wide), assume the formatter is broken and give up."
    },
