      "updated_at": "2016-05-03 07:34:50 UTC",
      "body": "I think 80 chars is definitely uncommon for typical Scala, but it is far superior to 100+ column limit as it forces you to refactor horribly big/nested expressions sooner. Scala code in the wild goes way overboard with nesting most of the time."
