      "updated_at": "2016-05-04 13:51:07 UTC",
      "body": "An alternative that came up at flatMap(Olso) is to introduce some sort of `--softMaxColumn` with default value 80 and `--hardMaxColumn` (current `--maxColumn`) with default value 100. It means scalafmt might choose to exceed to soft limit if it helps prevent very unfortunate breaks. I would need to look at diffs to confirm this works as I expect it to."
